    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-salmon-with-spinach-gnocchi/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>gnocchi</strong> and cook for 6-8 min or until beginning to crisp</p><p>Tip: Don't stir too often as this will prevent the gnocchi from crisping!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-salmon-with-spinach-gnocchi/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>salmon fillets </strong>(skin-side down), season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 5-6 min, turning once halfway</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-salmon-with-spinach-gnocchi/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and roughly chop the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>sun-dried tomatoes </strong>roughly</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-salmon-with-spinach-gnocchi/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> chopped sun-dried tomatoes</strong>\u00a0and <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> to the pan with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant and all the butter has melted</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-salmon-with-spinach-gnocchi/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, reduce the heat to medium and add the <strong>vegetable stock</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until the salmon is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Once cooked, add the <strong>blanched peas </strong>and <strong>cr\u00e8me fra\u00eeche </strong>and<strong> </strong>cook for 1 min further or until warmed through \u2013 this is your<strong> creamy sun-dried tomato salmon</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-salmon-with-spinach-gnocchi/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash the <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once the gnocchi has started to crisp, add the <strong>spinach </strong>to the pan and cook for 1-2 min until just starting to wilt \u2013 this is your <strong>spinach gnocchi</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-salmon-with-spinach-gnocchi/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy sun-dried tomato salmon</strong> over the <strong>spinach gnocchi</strong></p><p>Pour over any<strong> remaining sauce</strong> from the pan and finish with a few grinds of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
